element_texts.text:
Lemon
Hotel Schenley
Pittsburgh, PA.
May 9 of 28
My dear Miss {Pridlier}
May thanks for the kind note in response to my letter regarding dates for next fall. We are much gratified over the fact that you feel reasonably sure of giving us dates for next December - 1928- from Dec. 10th to Dec. 22nd and will hope for confirmation of these within the next few weeks.
Cordially yours
Julia B Whitney
(Mrs. J.E.)

element_texts.text:
Hotel Radisson
Seventh St near Nicollet avenue
Minneapolis, Minn.
May 28/28
My dear Miss Poullier.
Fearing you be writing me soon the confirmation or otherwise of the dates of exhibit for next December, I am writing to say that we leave for St Louis tomorrow and our address there will be c/o The King's Way Hotel - King's Highway - St Louis Mo. until June 11th.
Hoping to hear from you in the neat future. Ia m cordially yours.
Julia B Whitney
(Mrs. J. E.)
Dec 10-22 ok says Mrs Carpenter 6/2/28

element_texts.text:
Hotel Kings Way
on Kingshighway, overlooking forest park
Saint Louis
June 9 of 28
My dear Miss Jarnio.
Many thanks for your nice letter confirming the dates for next December - December 10th to 22nd inclusive -1928- for our exhibit of silver and furniture.
The cordial interest of Mrs. Leitner and yourself has been appreciated.
We are certainly looking forward to being with you all again and will endeavor to have as beautiful and exhibit as we have ever taken there. Some of our good Chicago patrons who have met us here in the last week seem delighted to know that we will be in Chicago in time for Christmas purchases.
With kind regards from Mr. Whitney and me for Mr. Leitner and yourself, I am
Cordially yours
Julia B. Whitney-
(Mrs. J. E.)

We must go slowly & think ahead on the possibility of having the caller continue to show while Lemons are entirely to themselves, they are the only people with whom we ever sign contract, they are as you know more than business like- We can't act lightly in it. We might get into endless trouble. It will take some thought.

Burlington Vt.
Dec 6th 1928
The Arts Club of Chicago
Wrigley Building
No. Michigan Ave.
Chicago, Ill.
Gentlemen:
Am forwarding to you today. Express paid, Mr. Joseph Winterbottom Jr.s pictuers to be used in your exhibit.
I have numbers the cases 1 to 6 inc. following is list of pictures and case number in which they are packed.

1 contains Prima Screen
3 pieces

Pat all his  & have his collection. Says mrs 12/22/28
